    \end{block}
    \vfill  
    
     
     \begin{block}{Summary}
     Our method predicts estimated means copies per partitions using Poisson or binomial regression. Afterwards, estimates are compared against themselves using t-test. Obtained p-values and confidence intervals does not require further correction, because the familywise error is controlled through the whole analysis. 
    \end{block}
